    "name": "Hyperbolic entailment cones",
    "description": "The text introduces a novel method for embedding directed acyclic graphs (DAGs). This method advocates for using hyperbolic spaces because they provably model tree-like structures better than Euclidean geometry. Furthermore, it models hierarchical relations as partial orders defined by a family of nested geodesically convex cones. The authors prove that these entailment cones admit an optimal shape with a closed-form expression in both Euclidean and hyperbolic spaces, which canonically defines the embedding learning process. Experimental results indicate that this method significantly improves upon recent baselines concerning representational capacity and generalization.",
